textDelta: What did the Moscow Treaty between Russia and the United States do to the number of nuclear weapons each country possessed? The treaty did not reduce the number of nuclear weapons possessed by either country.
How much of the world is forest in 2015? According to the World Resources Institute, the world is home to about 3.04 billion acres of forest. This is about 31 percent of the world's land area.
What place did Frederick Cook claimed to be the first person to reach in 1909? The North Pole

When Clinton was president, what was the policy on the Russian economy? The policy on the Russian economy during Clinton's presidency was to encourage privatization and to promote foreign investment in the Russian economy.

When I measured my body's composition with bioelectrical impedance, why did the electrical current travel faster through muscle than it did fat? The electrical current travels faster through muscle because muscle is a better conductor of electricity than fat.

When I measured my body's composition with bioelectrical impedance, why did the electrical current travel faster through muscle than it did fat? Why is muscle a better conductor of electricity than fat? Muscle is a better conductor of electricity than fat because it contains more water. The water in muscle acts as a conductor, allowing the current to travel through the tissue more easily. Fat does not contain as much water, so the current travels more slowly through the tissue.
